009package com.weather.sdk.exception;
010
011/**
012 * Exception thrown when cache-related errors occur.
013 *
014 * <p>This exception is thrown when:
015 *
016 * <ul>
017 *   <li>Cache initialization fails
018 *   <li>Cache storage operations fail (put, evict)
019 *   <li>Cache retrieval operations fail (get)
020 *   <li>Cache capacity limits are exceeded
021 *   <li>Cache eviction strategy encounters errors
022 *   <li>Cache TTL (Time To Live) management fails
023 *   <li>Thread-safety issues in cache operations
024 *   <li>Cache corruption or invalid data detected
025 * </ul>
026 *
027 * <h2>Error Code</h2>
028 *
029 * <p>Error code: {@value #CACHE_ERROR}
030 *
031 * <h2>Cache Configuration</h2>
032 *
033 * <ul>
034 *   <li><strong>Default Capacity:</strong> 10 cities
035 *   <li><strong>Default TTL:</strong> 10 minutes
036 *   <li><strong>Eviction Strategy:</strong> LRU (Least Recently Used)
037 *   <li><strong>Thread Safety:</strong> Concurrent access supported
038 * </ul>
039 *
040 * <h2>Recovery Actions</h2>
041 *
042 * <ul>
043 *   <li>Clear and reinitialize the cache
044 *   <li>Increase cache capacity if needed
045 *   <li>Verify cache implementation thread-safety
046 *   <li>Check for memory/resource constraints
047 *   <li>Implement fallback to direct API calls
048 * </ul>
049 *
050 * <h2>Usage Examples</h2>
051 *
052 * <h3>Handling Cache Exceptions</h3>
053 *
054 * <pre>
055 * try {
056 *   WeatherData weather = sdk.getWeather("London");
057 * } catch (CacheException e) {
058 *   logger.warn("Cache error ({}): {}", e.getErrorCode(), e.getMessage());
059 *
060 *   if (e.getOperation().equals("PUT")) {
061 *     logger.warn("Failed to store weather data in cache");
062 *   } else if (e.getOperation().equals("GET")) {
063 *     logger.warn("Failed to retrieve weather data from cache");
064 *   }
065 *
066 *   // Clear cache and retry without caching
067 *   sdk.clearCache();
068 *   return sdk.getWeather(cityName);
069 * }
070 * </pre>
071 *
072 * <h3>Cache Health Monitoring</h3>
073 *
074 * <pre>
075 * public boolean isCacheHealthy() {
076 *   try {
077 *     // Test cache operations
078 *     sdk.getCache().put("test", createTestWeatherData());
079 *     sdk.getCache().get("test");
080 *     return true;
081 *   } catch (CacheException e) {
082 *     logger.error("Cache health check failed: {}", e.getMessage());
083 *     return false;
084 *   }
085 * }
086 * </pre>
087 *
088 * @since 1.0.0
089 * @see com.weather.sdk.WeatherSDK#getWeather(String)
090 * @see com.weather.sdk.cache.WeatherCache
091 * @see com.weather.sdk.exception.WeatherSDKException
092 */
093public class CacheException extends WeatherSDKException {
094
095  /** Serial version UID for serialization compatibility. */
096  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
097
098  /** Error code for cache-related issues. */
099  public static final String CACHE_ERROR = "CACHE_ERROR";
100
101  /** The cache operation that failed (e.g., "GET", "PUT", "EVICT"). */
102  private final String operation;
103
104  /** The cache key involved in the operation. */
105  private final String cacheKey;
106
107  /**
108   * Constructs a new CacheException with the specified message.
109   *
110   * @param message the detail message explaining the cache error. Must not be null.
111   * @throws NullPointerException if message is null
112   */
113  public CacheException(final String message) {
114    super(CACHE_ERROR, message);
115    this.operation = null;
116    this.cacheKey = null;
117  }
118
119  /**
120   * Constructs a new CacheException with the specified message and operation.
121   *
122   * @param message the detail message explaining the cache error. Must not be null.
123   * @param operation the cache operation that failed (e.g., "GET", "PUT", "EVICT"). May be null.
124   * @throws NullPointerException if message is null
125   */
126  public CacheException(final String message, final String operation) {
127    super(CACHE_ERROR, message);
128    this.operation = operation;
129    this.cacheKey = null;
130  }
131
132  /**
133   * Constructs a new CacheException with the specified message, operation, and cache key.
134   *
135   * @param message the detail message explaining the cache error. Must not be null.
136   * @param operation the cache operation that failed (e.g., "GET", "PUT", "EVICT"). May be null.
137   * @param cacheKey the cache key involved in the operation. May be null.
138   * @throws NullPointerException if message is null
139   */
140  public CacheException(final String message, final String operation, final String cacheKey) {
141    super(CACHE_ERROR, message);
142    this.operation = operation;
143    this.cacheKey = cacheKey;
144  }
145
146  /**
147   * Constructs a new CacheException with the specified message, operation, cache key, and cause.
148   *
149   * @param message the detail message explaining the cache error. Must not be null.
150   * @param operation the cache operation that failed (e.g., "GET", "PUT", "EVICT"). May be null.
151   * @param cacheKey the cache key involved in the operation. May be null.
152   * @param cause the underlying cause of the cache error. May be null.
153   * @throws NullPointerException if message is null
154   */
155  public CacheException(
156      final String message, final String operation, final String cacheKey, final Throwable cause) {
157    super(CACHE_ERROR, message, cause);
158    this.operation = operation;
159    this.cacheKey = cacheKey;
160  }
161
162  /**
163   * Returns the cache operation that failed.
164   *
165   * @return the operation name (e.g., "GET", "PUT", "EVICT"), or null if not provided
166   */
167  public String getOperation() {
168    return operation;
169  }
170
171  /**
172   * Returns the cache key involved in the failed operation.
173   *
174   * @return the cache key, or null if not provided
175   */
176  public String getCacheKey() {
177    return cacheKey;
178  }
179
180  /**
181   * Indicates whether this was a storage operation failure (put, store).
182   *
183   * @return true if the error was related to storing data in cache
184   */
185  public boolean isStorageError() {
186    return operation != null
187        && ("PUT".equalsIgnoreCase(operation)
188            || "STORE".equalsIgnoreCase(operation)
189            || "ADD".equalsIgnoreCase(operation));
190  }
191
192  /**
193   * Indicates whether this was a retrieval operation failure (get, retrieve).
194   *
195   * @return true if the error was related to retrieving data from cache
196   */
197  public boolean isRetrievalError() {
198    return operation != null
199        && ("GET".equalsIgnoreCase(operation)
200            || "RETRIEVE".equalsIgnoreCase(operation)
201            || "LOAD".equalsIgnoreCase(operation));
202  }
203
204  /**
205   * Indicates whether this was an eviction operation failure.
206   *
207   * @return true if the error was related to cache eviction
208   */
209  public boolean isEvictionError() {
210    return operation != null
211        && ("EVICT".equalsIgnoreCase(operation)
212            || "REMOVE".equalsIgnoreCase(operation)
213            || "DELETE".equalsIgnoreCase(operation));
214  }
215
216  /**
217   * Returns a descriptive category for the type of cache error.
218   *
219   * @return a descriptive error category
220   */
221  public String getErrorCategory() {
222    final String result;
223    if (isStorageError()) {
224      result = "Cache Storage Error";
225    } else if (isRetrievalError()) {
226      result = "Cache Retrieval Error";
227    } else if (isEvictionError()) {
228      result = "Cache Eviction Error";
229    } else if (operation != null) {
230      result = "Cache Operation Error";
231    } else {
232      result = "Cache Error";
233    }
234    return result;
235  }
236
237  /**
238   * Returns the exception type description.
239   *
240   * @return "Cache Error"
241   */
242  @Override
243  public String getExceptionType() {
244    return "Cache Error";
245  }
246
247  /**
248   * Returns a detailed message including operation and cache key if available.
249   *
250   * @return a detailed error message
251   */
252  @Override
253  public String getMessage() {
254    final String baseMessage = super.getMessage();
255    final String result;
256
257    if (operation != null && cacheKey != null) {
258      result = String.format("%s [Operation: %s, Key: %s]", baseMessage, operation, cacheKey);
259    } else if (operation != null) {
260      result = String.format("%s [Operation: %s]", baseMessage, operation);
261    } else if (cacheKey != null) {
262      result = String.format("%s [Key: %s]", baseMessage, cacheKey);
263    } else {
264      result = baseMessage;
265    }
266
267    return result;
268  }
269}
